items.title: Phoenix needs over 150,000 apartment units — can we build them in time?
items.summary:
The future of Phoenix is looking packed, as it is expected to need 150,302 new apartment units by 2030 to keep up with demand, according to a study released in late June.  Phoenix will need to add 10,736 apartment units per year on average in the coming years to meet this projected demand, according to a study released by the Arizona Multihousing Association (AMA) and National Apartment Association (NAA).  The Phoenix area’s accelerating population growth, a!
